==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mallee bird
<hw>mal*lee" bird`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <ety>[From
native name.]</ety> <def>The leipoa, or Australian moundbird; it
incubates eggs naturally in sandy mounds. See <er>Leipoa</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mallee fowl, mallee-fowl, leipoa, lowan, <spn>Leipoa
ocellata</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mallee fowl</ent>⟦br⟧
